solution: ```class Solution {
    public int hammingWeight(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n != 0) {
            n &= (n - 1);
            count++;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(k) where k is the number of set bits
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses Brian Kernighan's algorithm which repeatedly clears the least-significant set bit, counting each iteration. This is optimal for sparse bit patterns and avoids examining every bit.

